entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what are some things you like to do for fun

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: walk along the beach bike riding

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is great what are some things that make you really mad

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: arrogant people

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what do you do when you are annoyed

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i try not to get angry but sometimes i do try to learn i am learning to walk away from things but sometimes people provoke you

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: yeah how are you at controlling your temper

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i am getting better i would say seventy five percent under control

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is good when was the last time you argued with someone and what was it about

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: oh about a month ago with my daughter and her finances

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what is one of your most memorable experiences

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: waking up when my kids were younger on christmas day i loved it

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is so good to hear have you ever served in the military

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you ever been diagnosed with ptsd

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yes

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how long ago were you diagnosed

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: it is been exactly two years and two months

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what got you to seek help

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: loneliness depression especially after i did not have any family members left in the united states so i went to a counselor and then to group therapy

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: yeah do you feel like therapy is useful

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yes

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: can you tell me about that

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i mostly enjoy group therapy because you are sitting in a group with other people talking about your your likes your dislikes your problems and sometimes somebody else is sharing going through the same thing you are and you can share you know share what you are going through and what can help make it better

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: yeah how has seeing a therapist affected you

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: it is affected me a lot it is helped me cope with things it is nice to have somebody else to talk to

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is great did you think you had a problem before you found out

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yes i did not want to admit it but after awhile and feeling depressed for so long i knew i had to do something

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how have you been feeling lately

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: pretty good

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you noticed any changes in your behavior or thoughts lately

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no just getting more positive better
